ust hold the CONTROL key down as well as the SELECT mouse What are the default key bindings in textedit and elsewhere See the man page for textedit for some of In general the editing moving commands go in the opposite direction when shifted Ctrl w deletes a word and Ctrl W deletes the word to the right of the insert Meta i include file Meta f find selection forward backward Ctrl a start of line Ctrl back word Ctrl e end of line Ctrl forward word Ctrl w delete word Ctrl u delete to start END of line Ctrl Return move to end START of document See the O'Reilly XView Reference Manual for a list of some of the default keys see also the olwm or olvwm manual What can I put in my Where is it documented See the manual page for Subject Applications Finding Contact SunSoft or Sun and ask for the Catalyst OPEN LOOK guide which lists over pages of applications and also the huge Catalyst listing of products for Suns updated six Sun's free CDWare CD ROMs each contain demo versions of several popular OPEN LOOK Often you can simply contact the vendor concerned to have the license upgraded from demo and receive the full product SunPICS produces a CD ROM for NeWSPrint users Printer's Pallate which contains NeWSprint drivers for a variety of printers and plotters as well as scaleable fonts that you can There is a separate FAQ posting in look that lists a number of free and commercial aplications mail for a copy including OPEN LOOK UI Application List in the Subject for a faster Subject DeskSet Mailtool Calendar Manager Is there a tty based interface to cm Calendar Manager Yes cm delete cm insert and cm lookup these all have manual If man cm delete doesn't work or gives strange messages see under Trouble Shooting Strange Error Messages How can I arrange to have my included in my outgoing mail The best way is cd cp usr lib chmod w edit use vi textedit or whatever you prefer add the follwing KEY RIGHT FILTER cat you might need to change to HOME Now pressing will insert your Subject Fonts D